<H1>Example of using the || operator</H1>

<P>To send a message to a user using the appropriate utility:</P>

<PRE WIDTH=80>   <STRONG>cat writemail</STRONG>
   #!/bin/sh
   # usage: writemail user message
   echo "$2" |{ write "$1" || mail "$1" ;} 
</PRE>

<P>The user types a command such as:</P>

<PRE WIDTH=80>   <STRONG>writemail sarah 'call me'</STRONG>
</PRE>

<P>The message entered by the user is <A HREF="../commanz/cmd4.html">piped</A>
through the command <SAMP>{ write "$1" || mail "$1" ; }</SAMP>.</P>

<P>If the the message cannot be sent to the user's terminal
(they are not logged on) with the command <SAMP>write "$1"</SAMP> then
the message is sent to the user by <A HREF="../mail/index.html">mail</A>.</P>

